nl.uu.cs.ape.sat.automaton

Class State

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.uu.cs.ape.sat.automaton.State
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Predicate

    public class State
extends java.lang.Object
implements Predicate
    Class is used to represent the states in module and type automatons. Automaton corresponds to the structure of the possible solutions of the synthesis, i.e. it represents the structure that the provided solutions will follow.

    Labeling of the automaton is provided in /APE/res/WorkflowAutomaton_Implementation.png
    Author:
    Vedran Kasalica

      • getAbsoluteStateNumber

        public int getAbsoluteStateNumber()
        Returns the absolute order number of the state within the whole workflow. Unlike getStateNumber, this function returns number that can be used to compare ordering of any 2 states in the system, disregarding the block or their type (data type, tool, etc.). NULL state has AbsoluteStateNumber -1.
        Returns:
        Non-negative number that corresponds to the absolute order number of the state or -1 for NULL state.
